{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/smartcert/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Sebastian Klingler | UI Engineer","author":"Sebastian Klingler"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"f20d5490-bffc-5906-aaf7-2621acf04f5a","html":"<p><a href=\"https://www.smartcert.app/\">SmartCert</a> is a decentralized application that allows corporations to issue certifications and individuals to provably display those certifications.</p>\n<p>Upon receiving a certification (from Amazon for example), the burden of proof lies with whomever is trying to verify that you hold that certification. A prospective employer would need to contact Amazon and provide the number associated with your certification to verify that you actually received it.</p>\n<p>SmartCert utilizes the blockchain to make this process trust-less. The certifications are distributed from an issuer address to a holder address. Verification then becomes as simple as signing a message to prove ownership of the address holding the certification.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/07be73c98449aac3220a166f71e6ddd1/c0ee2/smartcert.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 43.417085427135675%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"SmartCert\"\n        title=\"SmartCert\"\n        src=\"/static/07be73c98449aac3220a166f71e6ddd1/799d3/smartcert.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/07be73c98449aac3220a166f71e6ddd1/00d96/smartcert.png 148w,\n/static/07be73c98449aac3220a166f71e6ddd1/0b23c/smartcert.png 295w,\n/static/07be73c98449aac3220a166f71e6ddd1/799d3/smartcert.png 590w,\n/static/07be73c98449aac3220a166f71e6ddd1/2a3d6/smartcert.png 885w,\n/static/07be73c98449aac3220a166f71e6ddd1/c0ee2/smartcert.png 995w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Stack</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/\">React</a> was used to build the views and display blockchain data.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://redux.js.org/\">Redux</a> was used as the state container along with <a href=\"https://github.com/trufflesuite/drizzle\">Drizzle</a> to sync with the state of the deployed smart contract. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://solidity.readthedocs.io/\">Solidity</a> was used to develop the smart contract containing the business logic.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://truffleframework.com/\">Truffle</a> was used to deploy SmartCert on the Ropsten test net.</p>\n<h1>Contribute</h1>\n<p>Iâ€™m open to any and all contribution! Find the repo <a href=\"https://gitlab.com/sliptype/smartcert\">here</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"SmartCert","date":"May 28, 2018"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/smartcert/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/tacky/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Tacky"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/styling-in-cyclejs/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Styling in Cycle.js"}}}}}